OL,3,CNew rules passed on declaring
OL,4,Cpolitical groups as Jersey's election
OL,5,Clooms
OL,7,FCandidates in this year's general
OL,8,Felection in Jersey will be asked to
OL,9,Fdeclare if they're a member of a non-
OL,10,Fparty political group.
OL,12,FIt comes after a vote in the States of
OL,13,FJersey this week to introduce a new
OL,14,Fvoluntary code of practice.
OL,16,FSince registration laws were
OL,17,Fintroduced to the island in 2008,
OL,18,Fanyone standing as part of a political
OL,19,Fparty has had to declare that publicly.
